cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the security of information transmitted through the internet and proposes a new keyed hash function to address security flaws in the current standard. This is a clear indication that the paper belongs to the Cryptography and Security sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of hash functions to secure information transmitted through the internet. Information theory deals with the quantification, storage, and communication of information, which is relevant to the topic of the paper.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new hash function based on chaotic iterations, which is a technique used in systems and control theory. The paper also discusses the topological properties of the hash function, which are relevant to systems and control.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new hash function and discusses its performance. This is relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms sub-category.
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses the use of chaotic iterations in the proposed hash function. Chaotic iterations are a technique used in numerical analysis, which is relevant to the topic of the paper.
